1
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,200
You're twisting words.

2
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,000
It's malicious slander.

3
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,160
Watch out, or the ghosts will come for you.

4
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:19,720
Where did this wench come from?

5
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:21,160
How dare you curse me?

6
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:24,320
Watch out, or I'll have the Great Immortal deal with you.

7
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:27,800
The Great Immortal hates adulteresses like you the most.

8
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:30,210
Madam, why is your tongue so sharp?

9
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,160
Miss.

10
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,560
You mustn't say that.

11
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,400
She is the wife of our local Great Immortal.

12
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:37,160
She serves the Great Immortal personally.

13
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:38,080
So what?

14
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,680
And who are you?

15
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,320
Are you jealous?

16
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,860
You're actually jealous.

17
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,440
I am his lawful wife.

18
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:52,850
I can guarantee,

19
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,600
that apart from me,

20
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:57,570
my husband has nothing to do with any other woman.

21
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,160
You...

22
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,340
You're publicly bullying a defenseless woman.

23
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,980
She is so slight and small.

24
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,720
She's much shorter than you.

25
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,480
Even if she jumped,

26
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,890
she couldn't reach your ear to bite it.

27
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:14,800
Well...

28
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,600
Unless...

29
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,329
Unless what?

30
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:20,120
Unless you harbored ill intentions toward her,

31
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,440
and tried to force yourself on her.

32
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:24,079
She bit you while on the ground,

33
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,940
trying to protect her virtue.

34
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,000
Bullshit!

35
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,240
Fine.

36
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,860
Let me ask you this.

37
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,600
Since you claim she was smuggling salt,

38
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,920
where did she hide it?

39
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,220
How much was there?

40
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,100
Do you have witnesses?

41
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,010
Do you have physical evidence?

42
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,490
Since there is no evidence,

43
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,320
how did you officials

44
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,840
find her guilty?

45
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,320
Your Honor.

46
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,240
When I left the Capital,

47
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,160
I heard the Imperial Envoy sent by His Majesty

48
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:04,600
is on his way to Jinzhou.

49
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,600
He will arrive at the Wangjiapu Salt Field any day now.

50
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,840
Regarding today's events,

51
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:11,240
I suggest you tread carefully, Your Honor.

52
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,120
Cao Agou.

53
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,480
Was she really wrongly accused?

54
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,220
I was wrong.

55
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:26,940
I was wrong.

56
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,880
I know I was wrong.

57
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:28,880
I know I was wrong.

58
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,120
Rusheng, take twenty strokes.

59
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:31,960
Qiqigao, take twenty strokes.

60
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,040
If you do it again,

61
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,000
you will be dismissed and prosecuted.

62
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,660
Your Honor,

63
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,480
we know we were wrong.

64
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,240
We know we were wrong.

65
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,440
We know we were wrong.

66
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,120
We're here.

67
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,730
My two benefactors,

68
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,560
please stay for a simple meal.

69
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,800
We have urgent matters to attend to.

70
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,730
We can't impose.

71
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:12,920
Oh...

72
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,079
Then, benefactors,

73
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,220
next time you come,

74
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:20,320
let me treat you to a proper feast.

75
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,680
Here.

76
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,320
Take this for the road.

77
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:31,370
Don't go hungry.

78
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,090
Thank you very much.

79
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,520
Let's go.

80
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:41,880
Okay.

81
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,080
Take care.

82
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:44,880
Take care.

83
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:00,920
Sister Hui.

84
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,600
Who were you talking to just now?

85
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,680
My two benefactors.

86
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,660
Why are you in such a state?

87
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,720
I'm fine. I just took a fall.

88
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,260
Come inside, quickly.

89
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:38,360
We've been walking for so long without seeing anything unusual.

90
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:42,720
Could it be that Master Fang's righteousness

91
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,120
scared the ghosts away?

92
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:49,120
There must be something strange about these ghost rumors.

93
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,840
We must find the truth soon

94
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,440
to prevent further harm.

95
00:05:57,320 --> 00:06:00,520
You really don't know when to quit.

96
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,000
Two outsiders wandering the streets...

97
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,200
...are bound to alert the enemy.

98
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,400
I'm not cold.

99
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,320
Don't freeze.

100
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,360
And delay my journey.

101
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,440
Thanks.

102
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,520
It is actually quite warm.

103
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,659
No wonder you aren't cold.

104
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,159
Show some respect.

105
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:54,560
Stingy.

106
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,320
We should hurry and find a place to stay.

107
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,720
Today,

108
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,480
we offended the local Salt Official.

109
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:06,040
I reckon the shops on this street

110
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,720
won't serve us now.

111
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:13,480
No wonder every inn that saw us

112
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,730
closed their doors.

113
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:19,720
Looks like we're sleeping on the streets tonight.

114
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,560
The Jianghu Know-It-All

115
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,000
knows a good place to go.

116
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:26,730
Let's go.

117
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:40,800
This 'good place' of yours...

118
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:44,260
...is strikingly similar to that shady inn from the other day.

119
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,380
Since they are called ghosts,

120
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:49,520
maybe they are linked to this mass grave.

121
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,040
If we stay here tonight,

122
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,480
we might find some clues.

123
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,600
When I roamed the Jianghu,

124
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,920
I often slept in graveyards.

125
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,060
To shelter from the wind and rain.

126
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,600
In these desolate graveyards,

127
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,400
there's usually a small hut.

128
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,560
Only people offering incense

129
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,560
occasionally take shelter here

130
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,440
to warm up.

131
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:18,640
When you're away from home,

132
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:20,560
don't be so picky, Master Fang.

133
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:21,960
Let's go.

134
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,120
Why are you looking at me?

135
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,720
The Jianghu Know-It-All.

136
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,130
Lives up to the name.

137
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,600
Of course.

138
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,160
I'm not hungry. You eat.

139
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,280
Still so picky when you're on the road.

140
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,160
Tell me,

141
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,480
does Mrs. Hui really know nothing about the ghosts?

142
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,060
She says she doesn't, anyway.

143
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,640
Why?

144
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,600
Are you scared, Master Fang?

145
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,120
I'm fine.

146
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,000
If you are scared,

147
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:24,200
I can reluctantly lend you my shoulder.

148
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:29,120
You didn't mind calling me Husband,

149
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,660
so why mind a shoulder?

150
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,880
That's right.

151
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,640
Husband.

152
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,480
You...

153
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,640
That's in the past.

154
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,170
Don't mention it again.

155
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:08,900
Young Marquis.

156
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,280
Why are they so slow?

157
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,100
They still haven't returned.

158
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:16,860
Maybe they got held up by the Wang Family Shop business.

159
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,420
It's cold out here.

160
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,960
Let's go inside and wait.

161
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,160
Did you hear something?

162
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,200
I did.

163
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:08,600
Listen, it's the sound of ghosts weeping.

164
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,680
Stop it.

165
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,200
Who's there?

166
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,060
Sister Hui.

167
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:33,360
Oh, it's my two benefactors.

168
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,200
Couldn't you find a place to stay?

169
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,720
Why didn't you go to my house?

170
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,960
It's so cold here.

171
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,760
In the middle of the night.

172
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,000
Sister Hui, why are you here?

173
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,280
I felt upset today,

174
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,960
so I came to visit my husband.

175
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:03,440
The Salt Masters around here are all buried in this area.

176
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,240
Benefactors,

177
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:10,440
why not make do at my place tonight?

178
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,400
- No need.
- Sure.

179
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:20,970
Sorry to trouble you, Sister-in-law Hui.

180
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:26,800
No trouble.

181
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,480
We're here.

182
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,200
Come in, benefactors.

183
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,960
There are two small rooms in here.

184
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:52,760
I'll go tidy them up for you right now.

185
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,140
Just wait a moment.

186
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,450
No need, really.

187
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,220
Sister Hui.

188
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,960
You're finally back.

189
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,040
Sister?

190
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:13,360
Yan'er.

191
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,280
Yan'er.

192
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:23,960
Yan'er.

193
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,400
You must be hungry, Sister.

194
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,600
I'll get you something to eat.

195
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,400
No rush.

196
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:42,560
I never thought I'd find you here.

197
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,200
Do you know,

198
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,640
to find you, I...

199
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,000
Forget it.

200
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,610
Let's not talk about it.

201
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,850
It's all in the past.

202
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,360
I was kidnapped and brought to Jinzhou.

203
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,740
Bandits tried to rob me outside the city.

204
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,780
I escaped in the chaos,

205
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,360
and accidentally ran into the salt fields.

206
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,480
I met Cao Agou.

207
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:14,320
He tried to take advantage of me.

208
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,000
But luckily, Sister Hui saved me.

209
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,450
Thank goodness for her.

210
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,890
Thank goodness.

211
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,480
Sisters reunited.

212
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,940
Let's not talk about that.

213
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,720
By the way, Sister,

214
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,760
I heard Master Fang is your husband.

215
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:37,120
What? I wouldn't dare aim so high.

216
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:40,200
Today, I met a bunch of corrupt officials and bullies.

217
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,480
They were throwing their weight around.

218
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:44,080
I only pretended to be married to handle them.

219
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:49,970
So you really have nothing to do with Master Fang?

220
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,320
I'm traveling with them

221
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:55,920
just to find you.

222
00:14:58,320 --> 00:14:59,120
Yan'er.

223
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:01,000
Let's go.

224
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:03,720
I'll take you far away.

225
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,880
To a place where no one knows us.

226
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,280
We'll live well.

227
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:11,200
A peaceful life.

228
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:12,520
Okay?

229
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,000
I'm not going.

230
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:15,800
You go if you want.

231
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,640
No matter where I run,

232
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,320
I'll always be inferior.

233
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,360
Sister, you just don't understand.

234
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,020
I've always had a wish.

235
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:29,770
I must marry a high-ranking official.

236
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,280
And make those who trampled on me watch.

237
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:46,480
Like a misty dream.

238
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:53,360
A touch of moonlight sings to the breeze.

239
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,280
Persistence blooms in the silent night.

240
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:01,000
The youth of yesterday made a promise.

241
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,880
It is for love,

242
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:06,080
that a profound page is penned.
